        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:20PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 420 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Riverchase, or over Hoover. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Southern Birmingham, Hoover, Vestavia Hills, Pelham, Helena, Indian
Springs Village, Riverchase, Patton Creek, Hoover Metropolitan
Stadium, Ross Bridge, Bluff Park, Riverchase Galleria, Oak Mountain
Amphitheater, Oak Mountain State Park, and Shannon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
